    <h1>Fixed Income</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">OpenStax Principles of Finance (CC BY 4.0) · MIT OCW 15.401 (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A bond is a promise to pay known cash flows on known dates. Its price is the present value of those flows. Everything else &mdash; yield, duration, convexity &mdash; follows from that single idea.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: bond cash flow diagram -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
